  "texts": [
    "[14] by adding more layers (4 CLs and 3 FCs) and introducing batch normalization and dropout layers.",
    "Several hyperparameters were fine-tuned, resulting in an improved accuracy of 97.2%, surpassing the 94.9% accuracy reported in [14].Aljarrah et al. [44] experimented with a model featuring more CLs (6 CLs) and applied data augmentation techniques to the database.",
    "With data augmentation, the model achieved a recognition rate of 97.7%, a slight improvement over the 97.2% accuracy without data augmentation.",
    "However, the increased number of data and layers did not show a significant difference compared to the model in [43] with fewer layers and no data augmentation.The effect of adding more FCs was investigated by Altwaijry and Al-Turaiki [21], utilizing 4 FCs instead of 2 or 3.",
    "To mitigate potential overfitting due to the higher number of parameters, authors applied 80% dropout after FCs."
  ]
